		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Enchiridion meum familiare Gra[e]corum Apophthegmatum, et Prouerbiorum; pra[e]gnantiss[im]a
						minera insignium Dictorum, et Factorum. Nusq[uam] tantum
						ingenij, succincta[e]q[ue] Eloquentia[e], tantulo spacio.
					</marginalia_text>
					<book title="Enchiridion of Epictetus"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				With my familiar Enchiridion of Greek aphorisms and proverbs, a most pregnant mine of
				notable words and deeds. There has never been so much genius and fitting eloquence
				in so little space.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
